   1 from .base import DataView
   2 
   3 
   4 class Hash(DataView):
   5     """A hash.
   6     """
   7     __SCHEMA__ = {
   8         "__hash__": {
   9             "type": "list", "minlength": 1, "maxlength": 1,
  10             "schema": {
  11                 "type": "list", "minlength": 2, "maxlength": 2,
  12                 "schema": {"type": "string"},
  13             },
  14         },
  15     }
  16 
  17     @classmethod
  18     def validate(cls, data):
  19         super(Hash, cls).validate({"__hash__": list(data.items())})
  20 
  21     @classmethod
  22     def from_hash(cls, ins):
  23         """Interpolation to the hash result of `hashlib`.
  24         """
  25         return cls({ins.name: ins.hexdigest()})
  26 
  27     @classmethod
  28     def from_line(cls, value):
  29         try:
  30             name, value = value.split(":", 1)
  31         except ValueError:
  32             name = "sha256"
  33         return cls({name: value})
  34 
  35     def __eq__(self, other):
  36         if not isinstance(other, Hash):
  37             raise TypeError("cannot compare Hash with {0!r}".format(
  38                 type(other).__name__,
  39             ))
  40         return self._data == other._data
  41 
  42     @property
  43     def name(self):
  44         return next(iter(self._data.keys()))
  45 
  46     @property
  47     def value(self):
  48         return next(iter(self._data.values()))
  49 
  50     def as_line(self):
  51         return "{0[0]}:{0[1]}".format(next(iter(self._data.items())))
